      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SPECIAL SIAN (5) was quickly into stride and burnt early from out wide where she gave a sight, finishing third (19.59) and beaten 4 lengths over 350m at this track. Must come into calculations. JACK'S REGRET (1) is going well, finishing in the placings twice in a row. Not beaten far last time when a 1.3 lengths second (25.84) in a Grade 5 at Ballarat. Can hit the frame this time. MISS CHARMED (2) had a tricky draw last time and although midfield in fourth wasn't far away finishing 2.75 lengths from the winner (19.61). Strong form has emerged from her last run. Expected to give a good account. WILD VENUS (3) is likely to have admirers.",
